        <section>
          <title>Driverless car wars: what can we expect?</title>
          <chapter>
            <paragraph>April 1st, 2016: Tesla revealed its $35,000 new Model 3
              for the masses. The Tesla Model 3 will be self driving at least
              at Level 3 autonomy, equipped with batteries for 215-mile range,
              and powered by a network of chargers.</paragraph>
              <paragraph>The number of tech startups in transportation has doubled
                since five years ago. General Motors Co. and Fontanilis Capital
                have been investing in transportation startups for at least seven
                years, backing companies including Lyft Inc., Wheelz and Zendrive.
                Uber, Tesla and Lyft have formed during this time and existing
                tech titans Google and Apple have expanded their reach with the
                goal of creating autonomous, electric transportation on demand.</paragraph>
              </chapter>
