                      <section>
                        <title>Trump's effects</title>
                        <chapter>
                          <paragraph>Canada’s technology industry has chosen a
                            mascot for its latest campaign to poach Silicon Valley talent.
                            His name is Donald Trump. The ad-tech firm Sortable,
                            based in Waterloo, Ontario, Canada, also leveraged Trump
                            fears to appeal to expatriates who are considering returning
                            to Canada from the US. The firm made a broader appeal
                            in another digital ad that appeared on Facebook and Instagram.</paragraph>
                          </chapter>
                          <quote>
                            <author>bloomberg.com</author>
                            <text>Canada’s technology industry has chosen a mascot
                              for its latest campaign to poach Silicon Valley talent.
                              His name is Donald Trump.</text>
                          </quote>
                          <chapter>
                            <title>Anyone but Trump</title>
                            <paragraph>Republicans: Trump has personally criticized
                              Amazon and its CEO Jeff Bezos, he slammed Facebook CEO
                              Mark Zuckerberg for his immigration stance and he has
                              threatened to boycott Apple over its fight with the FBI.</paragraph>
                              <paragraph>Democrats: Sanders, who is vying for the
                                Democratic candidacy for the 2016 election, was even
                                a favorite among some of the technology industry’s biggest companies.</paragraph>
                              </chapter>
